 3. Licensing: Why GNU GPLv3?

Solutions that i found:
I chose the GNU GPLv3 license for "Ubuntu Modder" to protect the community.

- No Private Profit: 
No one can take this code, close it, and sell it as their own software.
- Stay Open Source: 
If someone improves a fix in this database, they are legally forced to share that improvement with the same open-source freedom.
- Freedom for All: 
It guarantees that these fixes will remain free and accessible for every student or developer forever.

What OS affected: 
Global (Legal protection for the project)
